{"lemma":"بَدَلاتٌ","slug":"بَدَلاتٌ","root":"ب.د.ل","root_slug":"ب-د-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-د-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"بَدَل","root":"بدل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":9,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","prep","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":19},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2002","n2008","n2009"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%8E%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to change, exchange, interchange"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mistake (one thing for another)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to take or give in exchange"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to change"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to invert"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to do one thing instead of another"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَدَلَ (badala) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of بَدِلَ (badila) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"compensation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"substitution"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"equivalent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"exchange"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"apposition"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"requital"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"generous, magnanimous"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"in exchange for, in compensation for, in lieu of, instead of","examples":[{"text":"كَيْفَ أَسْتَصْدِرُ جَوَازَ سَفَرٍ بَدَلَ ضَائِعٍ أَوْ بَدَلَ تَالِفٍ؟","english":"How do I obtain a replacement passport for a lost or damaged one?"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to have pain in the hands and joints"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gout in the hand"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"gouty"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew בדל (badal, “divide”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2002","headword_ar":"بَدَلَ","root":"bdl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badaAlN","text_ar":"بَدَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2, in three places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2008","headword_ar":"بِدْلٌ","root":"bdl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next paragraph, in four places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n2009","headword_ar":"بَدَلٌ","root":"bdl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidolN","text_ar":"بِدْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, T, S, M, Msb, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavalN","text_ar":"مَثَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivolN","text_ar":"مِثْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$abahN","text_ar":"شَبَهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ibohN","text_ar":"شِبْهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, T, S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nakalN","text_ar":"نَكَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nikalN","text_ar":"نِكَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the only other instances of the kind, i. e. of words of both these measures, that have been heard, accord. to AO, (S, TA, [but in one copy of the S, I find A'Obeyd,]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiylN","text_ar":"بَدِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) all signify the same; (S, M, Msb, K;) namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A substitute; a thing given,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"received,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"put,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"done, instead"},{"kind":"text","text":"of,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in place"},{"kind":"text","text":"of,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in lieu"},{"kind":"text","text":"of, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in exchange"},{"kind":"text","text":"for, another thing;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a compensation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalafN","text_ar":"خَلَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiwaDN","text_ar":"عِوَضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Kull:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badalu Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"بَدَلُ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albadalu mina Al$~aYo'i","text_ar":"البَدَلُ مِنَ الشَّىْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidoluhu","text_ar":"بِدْلُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiyluhu","text_ar":"بَدِيلُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxalafu minohu","text_ar":"الخَلَفُ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the substitute for the thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; (M, K;) i. e., another thing: (S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abodaAlN","text_ar":"اَبْدَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IDrd, Msb, K,) which, as pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiylN","text_ar":"بَدِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", has few parallels. (IDrd, TA.) Sb says, [making a distinction between"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badalN","text_ar":"بَدَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiylN","text_ar":"بَدِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a badalaka zayodN","text_ar":"اـِنَّ بَدَلَكَ زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily Zeyd is in thy place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but if you put"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badal","text_ar":"بَدَل"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiyli","text_ar":"بَدِيلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a badalaka zayodN","text_ar":"اـِنَّ بَدَلَكَ زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a bidaylaka","text_ar":"اـِنَّ بِدَيلَكَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily thy substitute is Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and a man says to another, Go thou with such a one; and he replies,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEiYa rajulN badaluhu","text_ar":"مَعِىَ رَجُلٌ بَدَلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"With me is a man who stands in his stead,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or who will stand &c. (M.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bala ka*aA","text_ar":"بَلَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badalFA mino ka*aA","text_ar":"بَدَلًا مِنْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Instead of, in the place of, in lieu of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in exchange for, such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badala A^ano tafoEala ka*aA","text_ar":"بَدَلَ اَنْ تَفْعَلَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Instead of thy doing thus."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abodaAlu","text_ar":"الاَبْدَالُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, S, M, K, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbudalaA='u","text_ar":"البُدَلَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Substitutes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lieutenants;] certain righteous persons, of whom the world is never destitute; when one dies, God substituting another in his place: (S:) certain persons by means of whom God rules the earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of seventy men,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"according to their assertion, of whom the earth is never destitute;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forty of whom are in Syria, and thirty in the other countries;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"none of them dying without another's supplying his place,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the rest of mankind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and therefore they are named"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbdAl","text_ar":"ابدال"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) accord. to Abu-lBakà, as stated by El-Munáwee, it seems that they meant [by this appellation]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the substitutes and successors of the prophets;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and accord. to some, they were"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seven, neither more nor fewer, by means of whom God takes care of the seven climates; one being successor of Abraham (ElKhaleel), and to him pertains the first climate; the second, of Moses (El-Keleem); the third, of Aaron; the fourth, of Idrees; the fifth, of Joseph; the sixth, of Jesus; and the seventh, of Adam:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA: [in which is also mentioned a treatise denying their existence, and disapproving of the assertion that by means of them God takes care of the earth:]) the sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badalN","text_ar":"بَدَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidolN","text_ar":"بِدْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badiylN","text_ar":"بَدِيلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IDrd, S.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Huruwfu Albadali","text_ar":"حُرُوفُ البَدَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The letters of substitution; those which are substituted for other letters; not those which are substituted in consequence of idghám."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) [The letters included under this appellation differ accord. to different authors: see De Sacy's Gram. Ar. 2nd ed. i. 33.] ―         -b4-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bidolN","text_ar":"بِدْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"badalN","text_ar":"بَدَلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,) applied to a man, also signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Generous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kr, * M, K:) and used in these senses, [says ISd,] they are, in my opinion, not devoid of implication of the meaning of a substitute: (M:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abodaAlN","text_ar":"اَبْدَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Fr","T","S","M","Msb","K","Mgh","Kull","IDrd","TA","Kr"]}]}}